---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Guide" active="guide">
  <div class="part-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Under construction, deliberately</p>
      <h1>The guide</h1>
      <p class="lede prose">Craft guides for narrative and descriptive writing: openings, structure, imagery, sentence control and endings. This site is growing: the framework is here, and the craft guides arrive as the unit is taught.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section class="band">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Planned contents</h2>
      <ul class="tick">
        <li>Openings that earn attention (and clichés to avoid)</li>
        <li>Structure: shape, time, tension and the placed detail</li>
        <li>Sentence craft: variety, control and deliberate rule-breaking</li>
        <li>Endings: landing a piece rather than stopping it</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each guide follows the family method: what the text or form is doing, the methods that
      matter, and analysis that always moves from device to effect.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
